Cell["\<\
This version turns integers into strings of the length specified by the \
number of digits previously determined, but it still treats single digits as \
numbers, and will ignore initial 0s in the input. Consider treating all \
numeric strings as strings, or import them from strings and store them \
wrapped in a new type NumericList\
\>", "Text",
