Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
I want to create a new function/object Numeric, which will be wrapper for a \
list of integers. The DisplayForm for these objects will show the elements of \
the list side-by-side, with no space between them. We will also (later) \
operate on Numeric objects, adding two of them to create a new one, or \
multiplying a Numeric by an integer to create a new Numeric.\
\>", "ChatInput",
 CellDingbat->Cell[
   BoxData[
    DynamicBox[
     ToBoxes[
      If[
       TrueQ[CloudSystem`$CloudNotebooks], 
       RawBoxes[
        TemplateBox[{}, "ChatIconUser"]], 
       RawBoxes[
        TemplateBox[{}, "ChatInputCellDingbat"]]], StandardForm]]], 
   Background -> None, CellFrame -> 0, CellMargins -> 0],
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9812045009416714`*^9, 3.9812045183700657`*^9}, {
  3.981204606075596*^9, 3.9812046484394093`*^9}, {3.981205241936775*^9, 
  3.981205242552868*^9}, {3.98120536726589*^9, 3.9812054200381927`*^9}, {
  3.981205603426193*^9, 3.981205624912895*^9}, {3.981205701441305*^9, 
  3.9812057055724926`*^9}, {3.9812057688616257`*^9, 3.9812057997444706`*^9}, {
  3.9812059352167015`*^9, 3.9812059771556873`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[104]:=",ExpressionUUID->"22ba6b2e-b3fe-4c4a-8667-a86fc6957fc1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To create a new function or object ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
   "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
  "e4791fab-dbea-2e47-880d-57ac9ed69b76"],
 " that acts as a wrapper for a list of integers and provides a custom \
display and arithmetic operations, we can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Define \
the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
   "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
  "8aaa57cc-e0df-2d45-83cf-33989325bf11"],
 " Object**: Create a new data structure that stores a list of integers.\n2. ",
 StyleBox["Custom Display",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Implement a custom display for this object using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
   "MakeBoxes", "paclet:ref/MakeBoxes", 
    "https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/MakeBoxes.html"},
   "TextRefLink"]],ExpressionUUID->"3521a5df-5a61-304f-8bd6-35d7eeb5a643"],
 ".\n3. ",
 StyleBox["Arithmetic Operations",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Define methods for arithmetic operations like addition and \
multiplication.\n\nHere's a basic implementation: \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     BoxData[
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
          
          RowBox[{"Define", " ", "the", " ", "Numeric", " ", "object", " ", 
            "as", " ", "a", " ", "wrapper", " ", "for", " ", "a", " ", "list",
             " ", "of", " ", "integers"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "Numeric", "]"}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"MakeBoxes", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", "list_List", "]"}], ",", "form_"}], 
                "]"}], ":=", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"With", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    RowBox[{"str", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"StringJoin", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"ToString", " ", "/@", " ", "list"}], "]"}]}], 
                    "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                  RowBox[{"InterpretationBox", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"str", ",", 
                    RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", "list", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
                "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            
            RowBox[{"Create", " ", "an", " ", "addition", " ", "operation", 
              " ", "for", " ", "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], " ", "*)"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"Plus", "[", 
                RowBox[{"n1_Numeric", ",", "n2_Numeric"}], "]"}], ":=", 
              "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"IntegerDigits", "[", 
                  RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n1", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], "+", 
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n2", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
            ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            
            RowBox[{"Create", " ", "a", " ", "multiplication", " ", 
              "operation", " ", "for", " ", "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], " ", 
            "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"Times", "[", 
                RowBox[{"n_Numeric", ",", "k_Integer"}], "]"}], ":=", 
              "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"IntegerDigits", "[", 
                  RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], "*", "k"}], "]"}], 
                "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{"Example", " ", "usage"}], " ", "*)"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"n1", "=", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"{", 
                  RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "3"}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"n2", "=", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"{", 
                  RowBox[{"4", ",", "5", ",", "6"}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{"Display", " ", "the", " ", "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], 
            " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"n1", ",", "n2"}], "}"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            
            RowBox[{"Add", " ", "and", " ", "multiply", " ", "Numeric", " ", 
              "objects"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"n1", "+", "n2"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"n1", "*", "3"}]}]}]], "ChatCode", "Input", 
     LanguageCategory -> "Input", ShowAutoStyles -> True, 
     ShowStringCharacters -> True, ShowSyntaxStyles -> True, 
     TranslationOptions -> {"Enabled" -> Dynamic[
         AbsoluteCurrentValue[$FrontEnd, {TranslationOptions, "Enabled"}]]}], 
    "Wolfram"},
   "ChatCodeBlockTemplate"]], "ChatCodeBlock",ExpressionUUID->
  "6d05ec26-24ca-dd43-acd0-705d6cdd0ac2"],
 "\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  PaneBox[
   StyleBox["\<\"Explanation:\"\>", "Subsection",
    ShowStringCharacters->False],
   ImageMargins->{{0, 0}, {5, 15}}]], "InlineSection",
  Background->None,ExpressionUUID->"51bc2fa5-9139-a24a-a6ed-974dbcdaae20"],
 "\n",
 Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["\[Bullet]",
   FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
     GrayLevel[0.5], 
     GrayLevel[0.7533742]]],
  " ",
  Cell[BoxData[
   TemplateBox[{
    "MakeBoxes", "paclet:ref/MakeBoxes", 
     "https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/MakeBoxes.html"},
    "TextRefLink"]],ExpressionUUID->"fe6e3367-17c0-2f41-9520-93bae8fd835c"],
  ": This function customizes how the ",
  Cell[BoxData[
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
    "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
   "8215d166-4ab3-9049-86fe-126c93e47a48"],
  " object is displayed. It converts the list of integers into a concatenated \
string for visual representation."
 }], "InlineItem",ExpressionUUID->"68dcf9a9-9d06-b24d-849b-ee4bce173816"],
 "\n",
 Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["\[Bullet]",
   FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
     GrayLevel[0.5], 
     GrayLevel[0.7533742]]],
  " ",
  StyleBox["Arithmetic Operations",
   FontWeight->Bold],
  ": Define custom behavior for addition and multiplication. The operations \
convert the list of integers to a single number, perform the arithmetic \
operation, and then convert the result back to a list of integers."
 }], "InlineItem",ExpressionUUID->"ee073d59-9f41-2f43-8360-8286f5a56fb4"],
 "\nThis setup provides a starting point for your ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
   "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
  "338f3c2e-92bf-8741-8d96-bf33045ef39b"],
 " object. You can extend it by adding more functionality as needed, such as \
handling edge cases or implementing more complex operations. If you have \
further requirements or need assistance with enhancements, feel free to ask!"
}], "ChatOutput",
 CellDingbat->Cell[
   BoxData[
    PaneBox[
     TemplateBox[{}, "ChatIconCodeAssistant"], ContentPadding -> False, 
     FrameMargins -> 0, ImageSize -> {35, 35}, ImageSizeAction -> 
     "ShrinkToFit", Alignment -> {Center, Center}]], Background -> None],
 TaggingRules-><|
  "CellToStringData" -> 
   "To create a new function or object ``Numeric`` that acts as a wrapper for \
a list of integers and provides a custom display and arithmetic operations, \
we can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Define the `Numeric` Object**: Create a \
new data structure that stores a list of integers.\n2. **Custom Display**: \
Implement a custom display for this object using ``MakeBoxes``.\n3. \
**Arithmetic Operations**: Define methods for arithmetic operations like \
addition and multiplication.\n\nHere's a basic implementation:\n\n```wolfram\n\
(* Define the Numeric object as a wrapper for a list of integers *)\n\
ClearAll[Numeric];\nNumeric /: MakeBoxes[Numeric[list_List], form_] :=\n  \
With[{str = StringJoin[ToString /@ list]},\n    InterpretationBox[str, \
Numeric[list]]\n  ];\n\n(* Create an addition operation for Numeric objects \
*)\nNumeric /: Plus[n1_Numeric, n2_Numeric] := \n  \
Numeric[IntegerDigits[FromDigits[n1[[1]]] + FromDigits[n2[[1]]]]];\n\n(* \
Create a multiplication operation for Numeric objects *)\nNumeric /: \
Times[n_Numeric, k_Integer] := \n  Numeric[IntegerDigits[FromDigits[n[[1]]] * \
k]];\n\n(* Example usage *)\nn1 = Numeric[{1, 2, 3}];\nn2 = Numeric[{4, 5, \
6}];\n\n(* Display the Numeric objects *)\n{n1, n2}\n\n(* Add and multiply \
Numeric objects *)\nn1 + n2\nn1 * 3\n```\n\n### Explanation:\n\n- \
**`MakeBoxes`**: This function customizes how the ``Numeric`` object is \
displayed. It converts the list of integers into a concatenated string for \
visual representation.\n- **Arithmetic Operations**: Define custom behavior \
for addition and multiplication. The operations convert the list of integers \
to a single number, perform the arithmetic operation, and then convert the \
result back to a list of integers.\n\nThis setup provides a starting point \
for your ``Numeric`` object. You can extend it by adding more functionality \
as needed, such as handling edge cases or implementing more complex \
operations. If you have further requirements or need assistance with \
enhancements, feel free to ask!", "ChatData" -> 
