Cell[TextData[{
 "The issue you're encountering with the subtraction operation stems from the \
handling of negative signs in the output of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
   "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
  "2b548f11-86a3-a548-ab82-95e216bd8378"],
 " object. In the current implementation, the negative sign is being added as \
a string, which interferes with the conversion back to a numeric format for \
further operations.\n\nTo resolve this, we should handle the sign separately \
from the list of digits in the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
   "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
  "00f5ce9a-8689-e449-bef2-84275a6d924a"],
 " object. Here's how you can adjust the implementation:\n\n1. ",
 StyleBox["Store the Sign Separately",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Use a separate variable to store the sign of the number.\n2. ",
 StyleBox["Update Arithmetic Functions",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Ensure that arithmetic operations adjust the sign correctly and don't \
prepend it as a string.\n\nHere's an updated implementation: \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     BoxData[
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
          
          RowBox[{"Define", " ", "the", " ", "Numeric", " ", "object", " ", 
            "as", " ", "a", " ", "wrapper", " ", "for", " ", "a", " ", "list",
             " ", "of", " ", "integers"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "Numeric", "]"}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            
            RowBox[{"Custom", " ", "display", " ", "for", " ", "Numeric", " ",
               "objects"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"MakeBoxes", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", "list_List", "]"}], ",", "form_"}], 
                "]"}], ":=", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"With", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    RowBox[{"str", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"StringJoin", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"ToString", " ", "/@", " ", "list"}], "]"}]}], 
                    "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                  RowBox[{"InterpretationBox", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"str", ",", 
                    RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", "list", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
                "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{
              
              RowBox[{"Addition", " ", "operation", " ", "for", " ", 
                "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], ",", " ", 
              
              RowBox[{"extended", " ", "to", " ", "handle", " ", 
                "subtraction"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"Plus", "[", 
                RowBox[{"n1_Numeric", ",", "n2_Numeric"}], "]"}], ":=", 
              "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    
                    RowBox[{
                    "maxLength", ",", "sum", ",", "result", ",", "sign"}], 
                    "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                  RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"maxLength", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"Max", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"Length", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n1", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
                    RowBox[{"Length", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n2", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"sum", "=", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n1", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], "+", 
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n2", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"sign", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"If", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"sum", "<", "0"}], ",", "\"-\"", ",", "\"\""}], 
                    "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"result", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"IntegerDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"Abs", "[", "sum", "]"}], ",", "10", ",", 
                    "maxLength"}], "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
                    "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"Join", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"{", "sign", "}"}], ",", "result"}], "]"}], 
                    "]"}]}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{
              
              RowBox[{"Multiplication", " ", "operation", " ", "for", " ", 
                "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], ",", " ", 
              RowBox[{"handling", " ", "negatives"}]}], " ", "*)"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"Times", "[", 
                RowBox[{"k_Integer", ",", "n_Numeric"}], "]"}], ":=", 
              "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    
                    RowBox[{
                    "length", ",", "product", ",", "result", ",", "sign"}], 
                    "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                  RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"length", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"Length", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"product", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"k", "*", 
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"sign", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"If", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"product", "<", "0"}], ",", "\"-\"", ",", 
                    "\"\""}], "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"result", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"IntegerDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"Abs", "[", "product", "]"}], ",", "10", ",", 
                    "length"}], "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"Join", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"{", "sign", "}"}], ",", "result"}], "]"}], 
                    "]"}]}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{"Example", " ", "usage"}], " ", "*)"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"n1", "=", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"{", 
                  RowBox[{"0", ",", "1", ",", "2", ",", "3"}], "}"}], "]"}]}],
             ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"n2", "=", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"{", 
                  RowBox[{"4", ",", "5", ",", "6"}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{"Display", " ", "the", " ", "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], 
            " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"n1", ",", "n2"}], "}"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            
            RowBox[{"Arithmetic", " ", "operations", " ", "with", " ", 
              "negatives"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"n1", "+", "n2"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"3", " ", "n1"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"0", " ", "n2"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"-", "n1"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"n2", "-", "n1"}]}]}]], "ChatCode", "Input", 
     LanguageCategory -> "Input", ShowAutoStyles -> True, 
     ShowStringCharacters -> True, ShowSyntaxStyles -> True, 
     TranslationOptions -> {"Enabled" -> Dynamic[
         AbsoluteCurrentValue[$FrontEnd, {TranslationOptions, "Enabled"}]]}], 
    "Wolfram"},
   "ChatCodeBlockTemplate"]], "ChatCodeBlock",ExpressionUUID->
  "1fe94b89-767e-ea47-853d-182ce2faad58"],
 "\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  PaneBox[
   StyleBox["\<\"Explanation:\"\>", "Subsection",
    ShowStringCharacters->False],
   ImageMargins->{{0, 0}, {5, 15}}]], "InlineSection",
  Background->None,ExpressionUUID->"fa81cffa-60f8-7b4f-83ab-23971e73749a"],
 "\n",
 Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["\[Bullet]",
   FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
     GrayLevel[0.5], 
     GrayLevel[0.7533742]]],
  " ",
  StyleBox["Sign Handling",
   FontWeight->Bold],
  ": The sign is managed separately and prepended to the list of digits only \
if the result is negative. This way, the numeric value is always consistent, \
and operations are not disrupted by treating a string as a number."
 }], "InlineItem",ExpressionUUID->"1098801e-82d2-da41-93e3-a8a798ffe7f1"],
 "\n",
 Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["\[Bullet]",
   FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
     GrayLevel[0.5], 
     GrayLevel[0.7533742]]],
  " ",
  StyleBox["Display",
   FontWeight->Bold],
  ": The negative sign is displayed correctly without interfering with \
numeric operations."
 }], "InlineItem",ExpressionUUID->"39d5cbfe-f06a-2047-bf86-e353c02896e6"],
 "\nThis approach should correctly handle both addition and subtraction, \
ensuring that the negative sign is managed without causing issues in further \
calculations. If you encounter any additional issues, please let me know!"
}], "ChatOutput",
 CellDingbat->Cell[
   BoxData[
    PaneBox[
     TemplateBox[{}, "ChatIconCodeAssistant"], ContentPadding -> False, 
     FrameMargins -> 0, ImageSize -> {35, 35}, ImageSizeAction -> 
     "ShrinkToFit", Alignment -> {Center, Center}]], Background -> None],
 TaggingRules-><|
  "CellToStringData" -> 
   "The issue you're encountering with the subtraction operation stems from \
the handling of negative signs in the output of the ``Numeric`` object. In \
the current implementation, the negative sign is being added as a string, \
which interferes with the conversion back to a numeric format for further \
operations.\n\nTo resolve this, we should handle the sign separately from the \
list of digits in the ``Numeric`` object. Here's how you can adjust the \
implementation:\n\n1. **Store the Sign Separately**: Use a separate variable \
to store the sign of the number.\n2. **Update Arithmetic Functions**: Ensure \
that arithmetic operations adjust the sign correctly and don't prepend it as \
a string.\n\nHere's an updated implementation:\n\n```wl\n(* Define the \
Numeric object as a wrapper for a list of integers *)\nClearAll[Numeric];\n\n\
(* Custom display for Numeric objects *)\nNumeric /: \
MakeBoxes[Numeric[list_List], form_] := \n  With[{str = StringJoin[ToString \
/@ list]}, \n    InterpretationBox[str, Numeric[list]]\n  ];\n\n(* Addition \
operation for Numeric objects, extended to handle subtraction *)\nNumeric /: \
Plus[n1_Numeric, n2_Numeric] := \n  Module[{maxLength, sum, result, sign},\n  \
  maxLength = Max[Length[n1[[1]]], Length[n2[[1]]]];\n    sum = \
FromDigits[n1[[1]]] + FromDigits[n2[[1]]];\n    sign = If[sum < 0, \"-\", \
\"\"];\n    result = IntegerDigits[Abs[sum], 10, maxLength];\n    \
Numeric[Join[{sign}, result]]\n  ];\n\n(* Multiplication operation for \
Numeric objects, handling negatives *)\nNumeric /: Times[k_Integer, \
n_Numeric] := \n  Module[{length, product, result, sign},\n    length = \
Length[n[[1]]];\n    product = k * FromDigits[n[[1]]];\n    sign = If[product \
< 0, \"-\", \"\"];\n    result = IntegerDigits[Abs[product], 10, length];\n   \
 Numeric[Join[{sign}, result]]\n  ];\n\n(* Example usage *)\nn1 = Numeric[{0, \
1, 2, 3}];\nn2 = Numeric[{4, 5, 6}];\n\n(* Display the Numeric objects *)\n\
{n1, n2}\n\n(* Arithmetic operations with negatives *)\nn1 + n2\n3 n1\n0 n2\n\
-n1\nn2 - n1\n```\n\n### Explanation:\n\n* **Sign Handling**: The sign is \
managed separately and prepended to the list of digits only if the result is \
negative. This way, the numeric value is always consistent, and operations \
are not disrupted by treating a string as a number.\n* **Display**: The \
negative sign is displayed correctly without interfering with numeric \
operations.\nThis approach should correctly handle both addition and \
subtraction, ensuring that the negative sign is managed without causing \
issues in further calculations. If you encounter any additional issues, \
please let me know!", "ChatData" -> 
