Cell["\<\
That still fails. Please redefine Numeric assuming it will have 2 keys, one \
for the sign (+1 or -1), one for the list of digits of the (absolute) value. \
\>", "ChatInput",
 CellDingbat->Cell[
   BoxData[
    DynamicBox[
     ToBoxes[
      If[
       TrueQ[CloudSystem`$CloudNotebooks], 
       RawBoxes[
        TemplateBox[{}, "ChatIconUser"]], 
       RawBoxes[
        TemplateBox[{}, "ChatInputCellDingbat"]]], StandardForm]]], 
   Background -> None, CellFrame -> 0, CellMargins -> 0],
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981209410718296*^9, 3.9812095008119354`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[267]:=",ExpressionUUID->"60361f69-d9be-d643-93a8-d403c8544929"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To address the issues with handling the sign and digits separately, we can \
redefine the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
   "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
  "a9af8b56-16f4-544c-9172-7d8fa62ef95f"],
 " object to have two components: one for the sign and another for the list \
of digits. This will help in managing the sign correctly and performing \
arithmetic operations more reliably.\n\nHere's how you can implement this:\n\n\
1. **Redefine ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
   "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
  "168ff9a3-9243-1e47-8b23-72550da0a2a8"],
 "**: Create a structure with two parts: ",
 StyleBox["sign", "TI"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["digits", "TI"],
 ".\n2. ",
 StyleBox["Update Arithmetic Operations",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Ensure that both parts are used correctly in operations.\n\nHere's the \
updated implementation:  \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     BoxData[
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
          
          RowBox[{"Define", " ", "the", " ", "Numeric", " ", "object", " ", 
            "as", " ", "a", " ", "wrapper", " ", "for", " ", "a", " ", "sign",
             " ", "and", " ", "a", " ", "list", " ", "of", " ", "digits"}], 
          " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "Numeric", "]"}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            
            RowBox[{"Custom", " ", "display", " ", "for", " ", "Numeric", " ",
               "objects"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"MakeBoxes", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"sign_", ",", "digits_List"}], "]"}], ",", 
                  "form_"}], "]"}], ":=", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"With", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    RowBox[{"str", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"StringJoin", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"ToString", " ", "/@", " ", "digits"}], "]"}]}], 
                    "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                  RowBox[{"InterpretationBox", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"If", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"sign", "<", "0"}], ",", 
                    RowBox[{"\"-\"", " ", "<>", " ", "str"}], ",", "str"}], 
                    "]"}], ",", 
                    RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"sign", ",", "digits"}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
                "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{
              
              RowBox[{"Addition", " ", "operation", " ", "for", " ", 
                "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], ",", " ", 
              
              RowBox[{"extended", " ", "to", " ", "handle", " ", 
                "subtraction"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"Plus", "[", 
                RowBox[{"n1_Numeric", ",", "n2_Numeric"}], "]"}], ":=", 
              "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    
                    RowBox[{
                    "sum", ",", "sign", ",", "result", ",", "n1Value", ",", 
                    "n2Value"}], "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                  RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"n1Value", "=", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"n1", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "*", 
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n1", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"n2Value", "=", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"n2", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "*", 
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n2", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"sum", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"n1Value", "+", "n2Value"}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"sign", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"If", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"sum", "<", "0"}], ",", 
                    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", "1"}], "]"}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"result", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"IntegerDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"Abs", "[", "sum", "]"}], "]"}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"sign", ",", "result"}], "]"}]}]}], 
                "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{
              
              RowBox[{"Multiplication", " ", "operation", " ", "for", " ", 
                "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], ",", " ", 
              RowBox[{"handling", " ", "negatives"}]}], " ", "*)"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Numeric", " ", "/:", " ", 
              RowBox[{"Times", "[", 
                RowBox[{"k_Integer", ",", "n_Numeric"}], "]"}], ":=", 
              "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", 
              RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    RowBox[{"product", ",", "sign", ",", "result"}], "}"}], 
                  ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                  RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"product", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"k", "*", 
                    RowBox[{"n", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "*", 
                    RowBox[{"FromDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"n", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"sign", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"If", "[", 
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"product", "<", "0"}], ",", 
                    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", "1"}], "]"}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"result", "=", 
                    RowBox[{"IntegerDigits", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"Abs", "[", "product", "]"}], "]"}]}], ";", 
                    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "    ", 
                    RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"sign", ",", "result"}], "]"}]}]}], 
                "\[IndentingNewLine]", "  ", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{"Example", " ", "usage"}], " ", "*)"}], 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"n1", "=", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"1", ",", 
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    RowBox[{"0", ",", "1", ",", "2", ",", "3"}], "}"}]}], 
                "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"n2", "=", 
              RowBox[{"Numeric", "[", 
                RowBox[{"1", ",", 
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                    RowBox[{"4", ",", "5", ",", "6"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
            ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            RowBox[{"Display", " ", "the", " ", "Numeric", " ", "objects"}], 
            " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"n1", ",", "n2"}], "}"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
            
            RowBox[{"Arithmetic", " ", "operations", " ", "with", " ", 
              "negatives"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"n1", "+", "n2"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"3", " ", "n1"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"0", " ", "n2"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"-", "n1"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"n2", "-", "n1"}]}]}]], "ChatCode", "Input", 
     LanguageCategory -> "Input", ShowAutoStyles -> True, 
     ShowStringCharacters -> True, ShowSyntaxStyles -> True, 
     TranslationOptions -> {"Enabled" -> Dynamic[
         AbsoluteCurrentValue[$FrontEnd, {TranslationOptions, "Enabled"}]]}], 
    "Wolfram"},
   "ChatCodeBlockTemplate"]], "ChatCodeBlock",ExpressionUUID->
  "470d9bad-20ab-b448-b766-7414238c9f52"],
 "\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  PaneBox[
   StyleBox["\<\"Explanation:\"\>", "Subsection",
    ShowStringCharacters->False],
   ImageMargins->{{0, 0}, {5, 15}}]], "InlineSection",
  Background->None,ExpressionUUID->"2f801183-d98b-bf4c-9973-3eda2b0633b9"],
 "\n",
 Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["\[Bullet]",
   FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
     GrayLevel[0.5], 
     GrayLevel[0.7533742]]],
  " ",
  StyleBox["Structure",
   FontWeight->Bold],
  ": The ",
  Cell[BoxData[
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell["Numeric", Background -> None]},
    "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
   "7a307514-d106-4f47-b7cf-a57119bbbdf0"],
  " object is now defined with a ",
  StyleBox["sign", "TI"],
  " (either ",
  Cell[BoxData[
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell["1", Background -> None]},
    "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
   "1b73a73c-edd3-9944-a7a5-75f96199223d"],
  " for positive or ",
  Cell[BoxData[
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell["-1", Background -> None]},
    "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
   "26603d68-f7a8-014d-8484-f397e669862c"],
  " for negative) and a ",
  StyleBox["digits", "TI"],
  " list, which holds the digits of the absolute value."
 }], "InlineItem",ExpressionUUID->"e7907c53-45e9-df41-b039-b714e1477e1c"],
 "\n",
 Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["\[Bullet]",
   FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
     GrayLevel[0.5], 
     GrayLevel[0.7533742]]],
  " ",
  StyleBox["Operations",
   FontWeight->Bold],
  ": Both addition and multiplication take the sign into account by computing \
the numeric values from the sign and digits, then adjusting the sign of the \
result accordingly."
 }], "InlineItem",ExpressionUUID->"86cb0f90-ee02-3241-9164-572934bd8d40"],
 "\n",
 Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["\[Bullet]",
   FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
     GrayLevel[0.5], 
     GrayLevel[0.7533742]]],
  " ",
  StyleBox["Display",
   FontWeight->Bold],
  ": The result is displayed with a leading ",
  Cell[BoxData[
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell["\"-\"", Background -> None]},
    "ChatCodeInlineTemplate"]], "ChatCodeActive",ExpressionUUID->
   "5f771afe-f12e-2e47-9373-fe89f26e2ff5"],
  " if the sign is negative. "
 }], "InlineItem",ExpressionUUID->"97a5def7-d2ca-9c48-bc7f-d75eda24d638"],
 "\nThis approach should provide robust handling of both positive and \
negative numbers for addition, subtraction, and multiplication. If there are \
further issues or requirements, let me know!"
}], "ChatOutput",
 CellDingbat->Cell[
   BoxData[
    PaneBox[
     TemplateBox[{}, "ChatIconCodeAssistant"], ContentPadding -> False, 
     FrameMargins -> 0, ImageSize -> {35, 35}, ImageSizeAction -> 
     "ShrinkToFit", Alignment -> {Center, Center}]], Background -> None],
 TaggingRules-><|
  "CellToStringData" -> 
   "To address the issues with handling the sign and digits separately, we \
can redefine the ``Numeric`` object to have two components: one for the sign \
and another for the list of digits. This will help in managing the sign \
correctly and performing arithmetic operations more reliably.\n\nHere's how \
you can implement this:\n\n1. **Redefine ``Numeric``**: Create a structure \
with two parts: `sign` and `digits`.\n2. **Update Arithmetic Operations**: \
Ensure that both parts are used correctly in operations.\n\nHere's the \
updated implementation: \n\n```wl\n(* Define the Numeric object as a wrapper \
for a sign and a list of digits *)\nClearAll[Numeric];\n\n(* Custom display \
for Numeric objects *)\nNumeric /: MakeBoxes[Numeric[sign_, digits_List], \
form_] := \n  With[{str = StringJoin[ToString /@ digits]}, \n    \
InterpretationBox[If[sign < 0, \"-\" <> str, str], Numeric[sign, digits]]\n  \
];\n\n(* Addition operation for Numeric objects, extended to handle \
subtraction *)\nNumeric /: Plus[n1_Numeric, n2_Numeric] := \n  Module[{sum, \
sign, result, n1Value, n2Value},\n    n1Value = n1[[1]] * \
FromDigits[n1[[2]]];\n    n2Value = n2[[1]] * FromDigits[n2[[2]]];\n    sum = \
n1Value + n2Value;\n    sign = If[sum < 0, -1, 1];\n    result = \
IntegerDigits[Abs[sum]];\n    Numeric[sign, result]\n  ];\n\n(* \
Multiplication operation for Numeric objects, handling negatives *)\nNumeric \
/: Times[k_Integer, n_Numeric] := \n  Module[{product, sign, result},\n    \
product = k * n[[1]] * FromDigits[n[[2]]];\n    sign = If[product < 0, -1, \
1];\n    result = IntegerDigits[Abs[product]];\n    Numeric[sign, result]\n  \
];\n\n(* Example usage *)\nn1 = Numeric[1, {0, 1, 2, 3}];\nn2 = Numeric[1, \
{4, 5, 6}];\n\n(* Display the Numeric objects *)\n{n1, n2}\n\n(* Arithmetic \
operations with negatives *)\nn1 + n2\n3 n1\n0 n2\n-n1\nn2 - n1\n```\n\n### \
Explanation:\n\n- **Structure**: The `Numeric` object is now defined with a \
`sign` (either `1` for positive or `-1` for negative) and a `digits` list, \
which holds the digits of the absolute value.\n- **Operations**: Both \
addition and multiplication take the sign into account by computing the \
numeric values from the sign and digits, then adjusting the sign of the \
result accordingly.\n- **Display**: The result is displayed with a leading \
`\"-\"` if the sign is negative. \n\nThis approach should provide robust \
handling of both positive and negative numbers for addition, subtraction, and \
multiplication. If there are further issues or requirements, let me know!", 
